Source: curses-apt-key
Section: admin
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Axel Beckert <abe@debian.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9)
Standards-Version: 3.9.8
Homepage: https://github.com/xtaran/curses-apt-key#readme
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/xtaran/curses-apt-key.git
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/xtaran/curses-apt-key

Package: curses-apt-key
Architecture: all
Depends: gui-apt-key | libgak-backend-perl,
         libcurses-ui-perl,
         ${misc:Depends},
         ${perl:Depends}
Description: Text-mode APT key manager (curses frontend for apt-key)
 This text-mode frontend for the apt-key utility (cak) provides an easy
 way to maintain digital keys for APT also on servers.  Those keys are
 required to authenticate Debian archives and prevent malicious
 packages to creep in.
